ROCHESTER, N.Y. - A meat packer has voluntarily recalled more than a ton of beef bologna that may be contaminated with listeria, the USDA announced Friday.
Consumption of food that contains listeria can cause listeriosis, an uncommon but potentially fatal disease, according to the United States Department of Agriculture.
The plant has not produced hot dogs or luncheon meats since Dec. 31, when USDA suspended inspection because the plant had not complied with sanitation requirements.
